ProblemIn commit fc96f1d029b45785fc3aafe5e543eebc48f1aaf0 the data structure returned by the BulkTranslationAI component was changed, breaking compatibility with the existing implementation in the offers module.Root CauseThe BulkTranslationAI component (src/app/components/bulkTranslationAI/Component.vue) was modified to transform API response data from:// Original structure (expected by offers)
{
  name: { 'pl': 'nazwa', 'de': 'Name' },
  description: { 'pl': 'opis', 'de': 'Beschreibung' }
}To:// New structure (incompatible with offers)
{
  'pl': { name: 'nazwa', description: 'opis' },
  'de': { name: 'Name', description: 'Beschreibung' }
}ImpactBulk translation in offers module stopped workingThe updateBulkTranslation method in src/offers/views/wizard/UpdateContent.vue:715 expects the original structureThe new extras module handler was written expecting the new (incorrect) structureFiles Affectedfrontend-vue/src/app/components/bulkTranslationAI/Component.vuefrontend-vue/src/offers/views/wizard/UpdateContent.vue (line 715-738)frontend-vue/src/extras/components/TranslationsSwitcher/Component.vue (line 339-352)Steps to ReproduceGo to offers moduleOpen offer editor with translationsTry to use "Bulk AI Translation" featureObserve that translations are not applied correctlySolutionRevert the data transformation in BulkTranslationAI to the original structure and update the extras handler to work with the correct format.Fix implemented in commit: 5ddc904296Additional NotesThe commit also accidentally included frontend-vue/public/sw.js which is a build artifact (removed in fix commit).

